comments: Siakam (TOR) goes through Collins' (SAS) body as he deflects the ball in the post.
Jones (SAS) touches the ball, which has a chance to score, above rim level after it has hit the backboard.
Schroder (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Jones (SAS) in the backcourt.
Johnson (SAS) briefly brings his off-arm toward Siakam and releases away as marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Anunoby (TOR) engages and disengages with Wembanyama (SAS) and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
While contesting the shot attempt, Barnes (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball, any additional contact to Johnson's (SAS) hand is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it is deemed Johnson (SAS) released the jump shot attempt before the shot clock expires. The shot attempt is ruled good and the game correctly resumes.
Collins (SAS) firms up over his right leg in Schroder's (TOR) path and absorbs the incidental contact during the pick.

Collins (SAS) is firming up and makes marginal hip-to-hip contact with Siakam's (TOR) while setting the pick. While going over the pick, Siakam and Collins make incidental foot-to-foot contact, Collins' foot is within the frame of his body.
Porter Jr. (TOR) firms over to his right leg in Jones' (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Porter Jr. (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position and successfully ties up Collins (SAS) and the ball on the play. A whistled jump ball is correct.

Replay review of the foul called on Siakam (TOR) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Siakam (TOR) is moving forward into Johnson (SAS), creating the foot-to-foot contact during the pursuit of the loose ball.
Siakam (TOR) briefly grabs and releases Johnson's (SAS) jersey as he moves through the lane.
After the steal, Barnes (TOR) request and is rewarded a timeout prior to any dribble violation.
